ackson vacated to move up to middleweight}}\n|- align=center\n!25\n|align=left | {{flagicon|Guadeloupe}} [[Gilbert Dele]] ({{small|v. Carlos Elliott}})\n|February 23, 1991\n|1\n|220\n|- align=center\n!26\n|align=left | {{flagicon|USA}} [[Vinny Pazienza]]\n|October 1, 1991\n|0\n|457\n|- align=center\n! colspan=\"5\" |{{small|Pazienza vacated after a car crash which kept him 3 months in hospital}}\n|- align=center\n!27\n|align=left | {{flagicon|ARG}} [[Julio C\u00e9sar V\u00e1squez]] ({{small|v. Hitoshi Kamiyama}})\n|December 21, 1992\n|10\n|style=\"background:#dfdfdf;\"|1169\n|- align=center\n!28\n|align=left | {{flagicon|USA}} [[Pernell Whitaker]]\n|March 4, 1995\n|0\n|118\n|- align=center\n! colspan=\"5\" |{{small|Whitaker decided to vacate and move back to welterweight}}\n|- align=center\n!29\n|align=left | {{flagicon|USA}} [[Carl Daniels]] ({{small|v. [[Julio C\u00e9sar Green]]}})\n|June 16, 1995\n|0\n|183\n|- align=center\n!30\n|align=left | {{flagicon|ARG}} Julio C\u00e9sar V\u00e1squez (2)\n|December 16, 1995\n|0\n|249\n|- align=center\n!31\n|align=left | {{flagicon|FRA}} [[Laurent Boudouani]]\n|August 21, 1996\n|4\n|927\n|- align=center\n!32\n|align=left | {{flagicon|USA}} [[David Reid (boxer)|David Reid]]\n|March 6, 1999\n|2\n|366\n|- align=center\n!33\n|align=left | {{flagicon|PUR}} [[F\u00e9lix Trinidad]]\n|March 3, 2000\n|2\n|435\n|- align=center\n! colspan=\"5\" |{{small|Trinidad vacated to move up to middleweight}}\n|- align=center\n!34\n|align=left | {{flagicon|USA}} [[Fernando Vargas]] ({{small|v. Jos\u00e9 Flores}})\n|September 22, 2001\n|0\n|357\n|- align=center\n! colspan=\"5\" |{{small|[[Oscar De La Hoya vs. Fernando Vargas|Vargas fought for Super title against Oscar De La Hoya]]}}\n|- align=center\n!35\n|align=left | {{flagicon|USA}} [[Oscar De La Hoya]] &ndash; {{small|Super Champion}} ({{small|v. [[Fernando Vargas]]}})\n|September 14, 2002\n|1\n|364\n|- align=center\n!36\n|align=left | {{flagicon|PAN}} [[Santiago Samaniego]] &ndash; {{small|Regular Champion}} ({{small|interim champ promoted}})\n|September 14, 2002\n|0\n|168\n|- align=center\n!37\n|align=left | {{flagicon|MEX}} [[Alejandro Garc\u00eda (boxer)|Alejandro Garcia]]&ndash; {{small|Regular Champion}}\n|March 1, 2003\n|1\n|287\n|- align=center\n!38\n|align=left | {{flagicon|USA}} [[Shane Mosley]] &ndash; {{small|Super champion}}\n|September 13, 2003\n|0\n|182\n|- align=center\n!39\n|align=left | {{flagicon|USA}} [[Travis Simms]]&ndash; {{small|Regular champion}}\n|December 13, 2003\n|1\n|525\n|- align=center\n! colspan=\"5\" |{{small|Simms was stripped of the belt in May 2005 because he filed a lawsuit against the WBA Organization (in November 2004) for not enforcing his mandatory contract that he received from the organization when he won the regular world title}}\n|- align=center\n!40\n|align=left | {{flagicon|USA}} [[Winky Wright|Ronald Wright]] &ndash; {{small|Super champion}}\n|March 13, 2004\n|1\n|372\n|- align=center\n! colspan=\"5\" |{{small|Wright vacated to challenge [[F\u00e9lix Trinidad]] at middleweight}}\n|- align=center\n!41\n|align=left | {{flagicon|MEX}} Alejandro Garcia (2) &ndash; {{small|Regular champion}} ({{small|interim champ promoted}})\n|May 21, 2005\n|1\n|350\n|- align=center\n!42\n|align=left | {{flagicon|USA}} [[Jos\u00e9 Antonio Rivera]]\n|May 6, 2006\n|0\n|245\n|- align=center\n!43\n|align=left | {{flagicon|USA}} Travis Simms (2)\n|January 6, 2007\n|0\n|182\n|- align=center\n!44\n|align=left | {{flagicon|CAN}} [[Joachim Alcine]]\n|July 7, 2007\n|1\n|370\n|- align=center\n!45\n|align=left | {{flagicon|PUR}} [[Daniel Santos (boxer)|Daniel Santos]]\n|July 11, 2008\n|0\n|491\n|- align=center\n!46\n|align=left | {{flagicon|ISR}} [[Yuri Foreman]]\n|November 14, 2009\n|0\n|203\n|- align=center\n!47\n|align=left | {{flagicon|PUR}} [[Miguel Cotto]]\n|June 5, 2010\n|0\n|97\n|- align=center\n! colspan=\"5\" |{{small|Cotto got promoted to Super champion}}\n|- align=center\n!48\n|align=left | {{flagicon|PUR}} [[Miguel Cotto]] &nd